info.headline: Wind Advisory issued December 29 at 9:24PM PST until December 30 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM TO 7 PM PST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. Strongest winds typically occur across exposed ridges and coastal headlands. * WHERE...Southwestern Humboldt, Southern Humboldt Interior, Southern Trinity, Northwestern Mendocino Interior, Northeastern Mendocino Interior, Southeastern Mendocino Interior, Northern Lake and Southern Lake Counties. * WHEN...From 1 PM to 7 PM PST Friday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
